OL,7,FAsked if Starmer believed the BBC was
OL,8,Finstitutionally biased, the spokesman
OL,9,Freplied: "No, but it is important that
OL,10,Fthe BBC acts to maintain trust and
OL,11,Fcorrect mistakes quickly when they
OL,12,Foccur, because as I say, for any
OL,13,Fpublic service broadcaster,
OL,14,Faccountability is vital to maintain
OL,15,Ftrust."
OL,17,FOn Monday morning, the former CEO of
OL,18,FBBC News, Deborah Turness, insisted
OL,19,Fthe organisation is not
OL,20,F"institutionally biased".
